# =============================================================================
# ADMIN-UI ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION (EXAMPLE)
# =============================================================================
# 
# ⚠️  IMPORTANT: You typically DON'T need to create a .env file!
# 
# The frontend uses window.location.origin to automatically detect the correct
# API URL based on where it's running. This means:
#   - On http://localhost:3005 → API calls go to http://localhost:3005
#   - On https://llmproxy.aitrail.ch → API calls go to https://llmproxy.aitrail.ch
#
# The SAME Docker image works everywhere without configuration changes!
#
# =============================================================================

# API Base URL
# --------------
# ONLY create a .env file if you need special configuration:
#
# Example 1: Native development with different ports
#   Frontend: npm run dev (runs on :5173)
#   Backend: go run cmd/server/main.go (runs on :8080)
#   → Need to set VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080
#
# Example 2: Docker development
#   → Don't create .env file at all! Use window.location.origin (default)
#
# Example 3: Production build
#   → Don't create .env file at all! Use window.location.origin (default)
#
# NOTE: This variable is IGNORED when using Docker because window.location.origin
#       is used instead. See src/lib/api.js for implementation.

# Uncomment ONLY if you're doing native development with different ports:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080
